<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1458] 64 commit logs as upper bound is too many -- make it half</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1458</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Running an upload, 64 commit logs as upper bound before we force flushes to clear the oldest edit is too much.  I can see an upload running in my little cluster and even after running for an hour we still have not hit the 64 logs max.  The more logs we have, the longer recovery on crash.  We should halve the number I&apos;d say.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
